    <section id="the-challenge">
      <h1>
        The Challenge
      </h1>
      <aside>
        A six-week challenge to find and present the patterns in 37 billion miles of data
      </aside>

      <p>
        The Metropolitan Area Planning Council invites you to visualize, analyze, and otherwise hack a dataset of <strong>vehicle ownership and mileage for every car in Massachusetts</strong>, the first dataset of its kind in the country.
      </p>

      <h3>
        What We're Looking For
      </h3>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Visualizations, animations, maps, infographics, games</strong>, and any other data-driven medium that reveals patterns and uncovers insights hidden in this vast dataset.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Answers to driving questions</strong> related to transportation, energy, land use, and policy, such as:
          <ul>
            <li>
              What makes a neighborhood more likely to have high car ownership and mileage?
            </li>
            <li>
              Where does driving place the biggest burden on family budgets?
            </li>
            <li>
              Where might investments in walking, biking and transit have the biggest impact in reducing how much people drive?
            </li>
            <li>
              What is the best way for communities to measure GHG emissions and set goals for reducing them?
            </li>
            <li>
              How is the average family's gas consumption changing over time?
            </li>
            <li>
              Do minimum parking requirements for new developments match up with vehicle ownership rates in different communities?
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>
        The Skills You Need
      </h3>
      <p>
        Whether you're a researcher, analyst, designer, developer, philosopher, what have you -- you can participate in the challenge. All skill sets are welcome!
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're looking to learn more about working with data, the morning of the <a href="#datathon">Datathon</a> will help you build new skillsets and reinforce existing ones!
      </p>
    </section>


    <section id="the-data">
      <h1>
        The Data
      </h1>
      <aside>
        The first dataset of its kind in the entire country
      </aside>

      <p>
        The data consists of five years' worth of annual vehicle-miles traveled, anonymized to the grid cell level, across the entire state of Massachusetts. We are also releasing five-year counts of the makes and models of registered vehicles.
      </p>

